{{Quote|In the days following the tragic and cowardly attack that claimed the life of this man, the news of our loss was overshadowed by the security policies it spawned. But Finis Valorum would never have backed such extreme reactionary measures and would have seen them as affronts to the freedoms he held dear.|A dedication to Finis Valorum read at the opening of the memorial by Senator Bail Organa|<ref name="Insider" />}}
The '''Finis Valorum Memorial''' was a statue made of [[marcluro-stone]] that was built in the [[Jrade District/Legends|Jrade District]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] in [[21 BBY/Legends|21 BBY]]. It honored the memory of former [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Finis Valorum/Legends|Finis Valorum]], who had been [[Death/Legends|killed]] in a [[Terrorist attack of 14:9:19|terrorist attack]] prior. The unveiling of the memorial was attended by an audience of 200 spectators, a low number caused by high security in the Jrade District. [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Bail Prestor Organa/Legends|Bail Organa]] read a dedication to Valorum at the unveiling.

==Description==
{{Quote|The Jrade Plaza surrounding the newly commissioned marcluro-stone statue has in the past held tens of thousands of spectators, but today's sparse gathering was dominated instead by the presence of clone troopers and Senate Guard security.|A HoloNet News report on the opening of the Finis Valorum Memorial|<ref name="Insider" />}}
The [[Finis Valorum/Legends|Finis Valorum]] Memorial was a [[marcluro-stone]] statue built in the [[Jrade Plaza]] [[Chancellery Walkway]] in the [[Jrade District/Legends|Jrade District]]<ref name="Insider" /> on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="Atlas">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] in honor of former [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] Finis Valorum.<ref name="Insider" />

==History==
{{Quote|Of course there should be more people here to pay their respects and remember former Supreme Chancellor Valorum today, but I imagine the nonstop Beta-level security alerts and endless clone patrols are keeping people indoors.|Senator Mon Mothma, speaking to HoloNet News|<ref name="Insider" />}}
[[File:ValorumPortrait-SWE.png|thumb|right|250px|Finis Valorum, whom the memorial honored]]
In [[21 BBY/Legends|21 BBY]],<ref name="Date" /> following Valorum's [[Death/Legends|death]] in the [[terrorist attack of 14:9:19]], the memorial was planned and approved immediately but was repeatedly delayed for several [[Standard week/Legends|weeks]] while the Jrade Plaza was shut down for security investigations in relation to the heightened [[Core Worlds Security Act]]. The Finis Valorum Memorial was unveiled on 15:01:13 to a small crowd of 200 spectators&mdash;including [[Senator/Legends|Senators]] [[Bail Prestor Organa/Legends|Bail Organa]] and [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]]&mdash;which was dominated by [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]] and [[Senate Guard/Legends|Senate Guards]].<ref name="Insider" />

Organa read a dedication to Valorum, in which he claimed that the former chancellor would not have supported the new security measures that had been introduced in response to the [[Terrorist/Legends|terrorist]] attack. In a [[HoloNet News Core Edition]] article published later that [[Standard day/Legends|day]], Mothma stated that more people should have attended and paid their respects, but they were likely kept inside by constant [[Cloning/Legends|clone]] patrols and Beta-level security alerts. The Director of Communications for the Jrade District, [[Dassa Borkannits]], attributed public trauma at the attack to the memorial's low attendance.<ref name="Insider" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Finis Valorum Memorial was first mentioned in "[[Republic HoloNet News Core Edition 15:01:13]]," an [[in-universe]] [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]] report written by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and published in the [[Star Wars Insider 73|seventy-third issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine<ref name="Insider" /> on [[December 26]], [[2003]].<ref name="SW.com">{{SWArchive|url=community/news/2003/12/news20031219.html|text=Mark Hamill On Stage In ''Insider'' #73}}</ref> "[[The Lost One]]," an episode of the [[The Clone Wars: The Lost Missions|sixth season]] of ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]''<ref name="The Lost One">{{TCW|The Lost One}}</ref> that first aired on [[March 1]], [[2014]],<ref name="Air date">{{WebCite|url=https://www.fernsehserien.de/star-wars-the-clone-wars/episodenguide/staffel-6/9660|text=Star Wars: The Clone Wars Staffel 6 Episodenguide|work=[https://www.fernsehserien.de fernsehserien.de]|archivedate=20190419012747}}</ref> portrayed Valorum as alive<ref name="The Lost One" /> in [[20 BBY/Legends|20 BBY]],<ref name="Fact File">{{FactFile2014|60|20 BBY 67-70|Sifo-Dyas' Legacy}} places the events of "[[The Lost One]]" in [[20 BBY/Legends|20 BBY]].</ref> thus contradicting his previously established death in<ref name="Insider" /> 21 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|BBY]] and leaving the [[canon]]icity of the Finis Valorum Memorial within the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity uncertain.<ref name="Date" />

